race.comment: ALTAR BOY (2) has been racing well without winning. His last two numbers stack up for this and he tumbles in weight. That brings him right into it. THE GIRL'S BOY (3) won comfortably twice and then tackled Open grade last time and found it too tough. Steps up to a longer sprint, but has won three times at the distance, and he's hard fit. Go well. VENTING (1) scored last time out with 1L in reserve at the end of 1600m. Yet to miss the frame in five starts over this course/distance and is a leading player again. FLYING START (4) is knocking on the door but needs to find a touch more to be winning.
